SIMPLE: heyday
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heyday
<hw>Hey"day`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>heida</ets>, or <ets>hei da</ets>, D. <ets>hei daar</ets>. Cf.
<er>Hey</er>, and <er>There</er>.]</ety> <def>An expression of frolic
and exultation, and sometimes of wonder.</def> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heyday</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Heyday
<hw>Hey"day`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. for. <ets>high
day</ets>. See <ets>High</ets>, and <er>Day</er>.]</ety> <def>The time
of triumph and exultation; hence, joy, high spirits, frolicsomeness;
wildness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>heyday</qex> in the blood is tame.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the <qex>heyday</qex> of their victories.</q> <rj><qau>J. H.
Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heydeguy</ent>⟦br⟧
